<description>Chris first shot to fame at Norwich City where he proved to be equally adept as both a central defender and a striker.
He was sold to Blackburn Rovers for �5million in the summer of 1994 and subsequently partnered Alan Shearer up front as Rovers won the Premiership title in 1994-95.
He later had a disappointing season at Chelsea before becoming Martin O'Neill's first signing for Celtic at a cost of �6million in July 2000.
 That fee proved a valuable investment as the Parkhead club went on to win a domestic treble in 2000-01.
Chris joined Birmingham City in January 2006 with a contract to the end of the season.
He followed Martin O'Neill to Aston Villa in October 2006 with a contract to June 2007.
Chris announced his retirement in July 2007 due to an eye injury.</description>

